properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 18 at 1:40PM CST until January 18 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Sioux Falls SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Winter Weather Advisory, blowing snow. Winds
gusting as high as 45 mph. For the Wind Chill Advisory, very
cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as 30 below zero.

* WHERE...In South Dakota, Clay and Union Counties. In Nebraska,
Dixon and Dakota Counties. In Iowa, Woodbury County.

* WHEN...For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 6 PM CST this
evening. For the Wind Chill Advisory, from 6 PM this evening
to noon CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The dangerously
cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as
little as 10 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
